# FlowTask Development Rules

## Must Read First

- Read `docs/IDEA.MD` and `docs/TECHNICAL.MD` before making changes.
- Read `docs/AI_AGENT_RULES.md` for AI agent behavior guidelines.
- Read `docs/CODE_QUALITY.md` for quality requirements.
- Read `README.md` for current project status.

## TypeScript Standards

- Strict TypeScript only. No `any` types.
- Use `zod` for schema validation.
- Named exports only (no default exports).
- Use `path.join` for file paths (cross-platform).
- Use `path.isAbsolute` (not `startsWith("/")`).
- Use `getShell()` from `src/utils/shell.ts` (not hardcoded `"sh"`).
- Use `spawn` instead of `exec` for long-running commands.
- Use atomic writes for state files.

## Do Not

- Do not implement full runtime logic in foundation setup.
- Do not create databases.
- Do not create web UIs.
- Do not add unnecessary dependencies.
- Do not skip tests.
- Do not bypass safety/validation rules.
- Do not mark task done without validation evidence.
- Do not hardcode Unix paths.

## Testing

- Write tests for all new code.
- Use `testDir` from `tests/setup.ts` (not hardcoded `/tmp`).
- Tests must pass before marking work complete.
- Run `pnpm quality` before committing.

## Architecture

- CLI commands must be thin — no business logic in CLI files.
- Core logic lives in `src/core/`, `src/validation/`, `src/executor/`, etc.
- Keep modules small and focused.
